COVID-19 infections are on the rise, but there's been no surge in hospitalisations. A recent Sisonke study has found that the J&J vaccine prevents 82 percent of admissions. Epidemiologist Salim Abdool Karim spoke with eNCA's Shahan Ramkissoon. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Professor Salim Abdool Karim says the country is in the grip of the fifth wave of Covid-19 infections. Karim warns that even with fewer hospitalisations no one should become complacent. "So no matter what criteria you use, we are in the fifth wave. Whether it is called or not, it doesn't matter because we are in a fifth wave," he said. READ: COVID-19 in SA | Cabinet concerned over spike in cases Over 2,900 new COVID-19 cases have been recorded. Gauteng is still leading infections with 1,386 cases. KwaZulu-Natal is second with 528 and the Western Cape is third with 417. Watch the video above for more details.